Package com.taco.suit_lady.view.ui.jfx.lists

Class CellControlManager<T,​C extends CellController<T>>

java.lang.Object
com.taco.suit_lady.view.ui.jfx.lists.CellControlManager<T,​C>
Type Parameters:
T - The type of element contained in the IndexedCell.
C - The type of CellController assigned to the IndexedCell.
public class CellControlManager<T,​C extends CellController<T>> extends Object

Used by an FX IndexedCell to help create, update, manage, and use a CellController to display its content.

Details

  1. CellControlManagers are always immutable.
  2. CellControlManager is used to manage properties and functionality that is present in both ListCellFX and TreeCellFX.
    • CellControlManager cannot be abstracted out into parent because ListCellFX must extend ListCell, and TreeCellFX must extend TreeCell.

  • Constructor Details

    • CellControlManager

      public CellControlManager​(javafx.scene.control.IndexedCell<T> wrappedCell, Function<T,​C> controllerFactory)

      Constructs a new CellControlManager for the specified IndexedCell.

      Parameter Details

      1. Wrapped Cell: IndexedCell<T>
        Refer to getWrappedCell() for additional information.
        1. Can be either a TreeCellFX or ListCellFX object.
        2. Immutable.
      2. Controller Factory: Function<T, C>
        Refer to getControllerFactory() for additional information.
        1. Used to retrieve a new CellController instance to assign to the Wrapped Cell.
        2. The CellController is automatically updated in the TreeCellFX and ListCellFX implementations of Cell.updateItem(Object, boolean).
        3. The Controller Property is automatically updated upon aforementioned changes.
      Parameters:
      wrappedCell - The wrapped IndexedCell.
      controllerFactory - The Function used to retrieve a new CellController instance for the Wrapped Cell whenever doUpdateItem(Object, boolean) is called.

    • doUpdateItem

      protected void doUpdateItem​(T item, boolean empty)

      Helper method called by the TreeCellFX and ListCellFX implementations of Cell.updateItem(Object, boolean).

      Parameters:
      item - The new item for the IndexedCell.
      empty - Whether this IndexedCell represents data from the list. If it is empty, then it does not represent any domain data, but is a cell being used to render an "empty" row. *Copied from IndexedCell*
